Name Origins:

The surname Skirvin may be of old Norse origin (possibly the name of a village), with many later instances of the name in the United Kingdom, primarily Scotland.  The earliest instances of the name within the United States are found in Maryland dating back to the 1720's.

Name Variations:

Some of the common misspellings or alternate spellings of the name are:

Skervin, Skirven, Skirvine, Skirving, Shirvin, Shirven, Skiruin, Scurvin, Scirvin, Skirvan.